<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-03-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-03-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="484" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d484">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-03-29"><hi rend="italic">March 29,
                                        1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>(Mr. Rockhill says that the under secretary for foreign affairs
                                informed him yesterday that the Chinese Government assents and that
                                telegraphic instructions will be sent, as department suggests.)</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>